  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-26 as a Phase 6 build-hygiene task after pre-existing test infra issue was
    flagged repeatedly during R4 by sub-agents executing tasks 050 + 053 + 054 + 042: the
    SprkChat test files cannot execute because `react-dom/client` cannot be resolved by Jest.
    This is a React 19 + RTL + Jest module-resolution drift that pre-dates R4 but blocks
    verification of R4 tests (`SprkChat.attachments.test.tsx`, `SprkChat.onAttachmentReady.test.tsx`,
    etc.). Operator approved adding to R4 scope (2026-05-26).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Test-infrastructure engineer familiar with Jest + React 19 + React Testing Library compatibility.
    The fix may involve jest-environment-jsdom version bump, RTL version pin, or `moduleDirectories`
    / `moduleNameMapper` tweaks to resolve the new React 19 import paths (`react-dom/client` was added
    in React 18 but its module resolution under Jest changed with React 19's package.exports).
  </role>

  <goal>
    All SprkChat test files (and any other React 19 + RTL tests in `@spaarke/ui-components`) execute
    without `Cannot find module 'react-dom/client'` errors. Test suite runs end-to-end. No
    production code modified. Existing tests pass.
  </goal>

