  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Reproduce">Run `npm test SprkChat.attachments.test.tsx` (or similar) in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/`. Capture the exact error message.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Diagnose">Identify whether the failure is: (a) `jest-environment-jsdom` version mismatch with React 19's new `react-dom/client` entry; (b) `moduleDirectories`/`moduleNameMapper` not resolving the new React 19 exports map; (c) `@testing-library/react` version incompatible with React 19; (d) `setupFilesAfterEach` or test-setup file conflict.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan minimal fix">Pick the narrowest fix: bump jest-environment, pin RTL to React-19-compatible version, add `moduleNameMapper`, etc. Document the chosen path.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Apply">Edit jest config / package.json devDependencies / setup files as required. Run `npm install` to pull any new deps.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify SprkChat tests">Run all SprkChat tests (including R4-added ones). 0 module-resolution errors. Existing passing tests still pass.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify other React 19 tests">Run other R4-touched test files that use React 19 + RTL: e.g., `@spaarke/ai-widgets` widget tests (task 042's DocumentViewerWidget). Confirm no regressions.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/test-infra-jest-react19-fix-2026-05-26.md` with: error captured, root cause identified, fix applied, before/after pass counts.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 068 status to ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Deviations">If the fix requires more than `package.json` / `jest.config.js` edits (e.g., test refactor), document why in deviations note.</step>
  </steps>

