  <notes>
    Pre-existing issue documented by multiple sub-agents across R4. Likely fix paths (ordered by simplicity):
    1. Bump `jest-environment-jsdom` to v29.7+ (React 19 support)
    2. Pin `@testing-library/react` to v16+ (React 19 compatible)
    3. Add `moduleNameMapper` to resolve `react-dom/client` explicitly if package.exports drift
    4. Switch to `jsdom` env with React 19's new server-component handling

    If pre-existing baseline already has React 19 + Jest working elsewhere in the repo, look at THAT setup
    (e.g., `@spaarke/ai-widgets` ran 14 widget tests successfully in task 042) and align.
  </notes>

